!! Basic graph

Standard tw-graph markup — works identically to vis-network:

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="A" label="Node A"/>
  <$node $tiddler="B" label="Node B"/>
  <$edge $from="A" $to="B"/>
</$graph>
```

!! Compound nodes (clusters)

The `cluster` attribute groups nodes visually inside a container:

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="Engineering" label="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Alice" label="Alice" cluster="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Bob" label="Bob" cluster="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Sales" label="Sales"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Carol" label="Carol" cluster="Sales"/>
</$graph>
```

Alice and Bob render inside an "Engineering" container, Carol inside "Sales".

!! Nested clusters

Clusters can nest — a cluster node can itself have a `cluster` attribute:

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="Company" label="ACME Corp"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Engineering" label="Engineering" cluster="Company"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Frontend" label="Frontend" cluster="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Backend" label="Backend" cluster="Engineering"/>
</$graph>
```

!! Property mapping from vis-network

All standard tw-graph properties work:

|!Property |!Example |!Effect |
|`color` |`color="DarkViolet"` |Node/edge color |
|`size` |`size="30"` |Node radius (Cytoscape width = size × 2) |
|`shape` |`shape="box"` |Maps to Cytoscape shapes (dot→ellipse, box→rectangle) |
|`arrows` |`arrows="to"` |Arrow direction on edges |
|`stroke` |`stroke="dashed"` |Edge line style |
|`label` |`label="text"` |Node/edge label (below node, on edge) |

</$fill>
